	<section id="presentation_audio" expanded="true">
		<audio id="narration01">
			<file play="true" bytes="50507" startpos="1" duration="148">a_03_02_01_010_01.swf</file>
			<transcript translate="true">Many parents wonder why it is important for children to learn to manage impulses and control feelings. They think their child will just grow out of it. However, self-regulation is a critical life skill.</transcript>
			<notes id="mentor-character">Narrator:</notes>
		</audio>
		<audio id="narration02">
			<file play="false" bytes="25295" startpos="1" duration="75">a_03_02_01_010_02.swf</file>
			<transcript translate="true">The better children are at self-regulating, the more successful they will be in school throughout childhood.</transcript>
			<notes id="mentor-character">Narrator:</notes>
		</audio>
		<audio id="narration03">
			<file play="false" bytes="59023" startpos="1" duration="173">a_03_02_01_010_03.swf</file>
			<transcript translate="true">Children who learn to self-regulate are able to delay gratification and suppress their immediate impulses. This allows them to think ahead to the possible consequences of their actions or to consider alternative actions that would be more appropriate.</transcript>
			<notes id="mentor-character">Narrator:</notes>
		</audio>
		<audio id="narration04">
			<file play="false" bytes="66243" startpos="1" duration="194">a_03_02_01_010_04.swf</file>
			<transcript translate="true">The years between the ages of 3 and 5 appear to be when children begin to understand the relationship between their feelings and their behavior. During these years, it is critical for parents and caregivers to help children identify and implement regulation strategies. </transcript>
			<notes id="mentor-character">Narrator:</notes>
		</audio>
		<audio id="narration05">
			<file play="false" bytes="37571" startpos="1" duration="110">a_03_02_01_010_06.swf</file>
			<transcript translate="true">Children who struggle with self-regulation, which is often independent of general intelligence, may face difficulty in transitioning to school.</transcript>
			<notes id="mentor-character">Narrator:</notes>
		</audio>
		<audio id="narration06">
			<file play="false" bytes="26799" startpos="1" duration="79">a_03_02_01_010_05.swf</file>
			<transcript translate="true">In this topic, the Key Message is that self-regulation develops gradually over the first years of life.</transcript>
			<notes id="mentor-character">Narrator:</notes>
		</audio>
